elements.description:
`uvalib-model-library`
data model for a range of weeks hours for a library location.

properties.name: library
properties.description: The library that is being requested.  If the lid property is not specified and the library property is, then this is used to define which Library is being requested.

properties.name: lid
properties.description: The LibCal Hours library identifier. If specified will define which Library is being requested (takes priority over the library property)

properties.name: startWeek
properties.description: Which week to begin with when selecting weeks. An integer value between 1 and 52.

properties.name: numWeeks
properties.description: The number of weeks to retrieve, if specified. An integer value between 1 and 52.

properties.name: object
properties.description: The location object as it is represented from the API.  If this property is set, the object provided is parsed and used. Otherwise this is populated from the API request.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Up to 52 weeks of hours data for a library location where each element represents a week of hours.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the Library location.

attributes.name: start-week

elements.description:
`uvalib-model-library`
data model for days in a week for a library location.

properties.name: library
properties.description: The library that is being requested.  If the lid property is not specified and the library property is, then this is used to define which Library is being requested.

properties.name: lid
properties.description: The Springshare LibCal library identifier. If specified will define which Library is being requested (takes priority over the library property)

properties.name: today
properties.description: Retrieve information for today only. If today is true then weekNumber is overridden.

properties.name: soonInterval
properties.description: Number of minutes before and after open hours for adding soon to current status (for today).

properties.name: weekNumber
properties.description:
Which week to use. An integer value between 1 and 52. This is overridden and set to 1 if the today property is set.
Note: Week 1 represents the current week and the LibCal API provides data out to a max of 52 weeks.

properties.name: object
properties.description: A week of hours as represented by the vendor API. If this property is set, the object provided is parsed and used. Otherwise this is populated from the API request.

properties.name: data
properties.description:
A week of hours transformed to an array with 7 (or 1 if today specified) entries of the following format:
  data[i] = {ymdDate: "YYYY-MM-DD", mdDate: "Mon D", month: "Month name", dayOfWeek: "Monday/Tuesday/...", hours: "8am-10pm", currentStatus: "Open/Closed/Closing Soon/..."}

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the Library location.

methods.name: _dayOrWeek
methods.description: This complex observer insures that the weekNumber is set to the first week ff today's hours are wanted.

methods.name: _dataChanged
methods.description: If the data has changed based on attribute values passed, then update the object data value.

methods.name: _processList
methods.description: Parse the object data to create the preferred data object for use in the UI.

methods.name: _nameChanged
methods.description: Used to update the name property when underlying data changes.

methods.name: _currentStatus
methods.description: Useful for the current day to identify if the location is open or closed. Returns one of the following values: open, closed, opening soon, closing soon.

attributes.name: library
attributes.description: The library that is being requested.  If the lid property is not specified and the library property is, then this is used to define which Library is being requested.

attributes.name: lid
attributes.description: The Springshare LibCal library identifier. If specified will define which Library is being requested (takes priority over the library property)

attributes.name: today
attributes.description: Retrieve information for today only. If today is true then weekNumber is overridden.

attributes.name: soon-interval
attributes.description: Number of minutes before and after open hours for adding soon to current status (for today).

attributes.name: week-number
attributes.description:
Which week to use. An integer value between 1 and 52. This is overridden and set to 1 if the today property is set.
Note: Week 1 represents the current week and the LibCal API provides data out to a max of 52 weeks.

attributes.name: object
attributes.description: A week of hours as represented by the vendor API. If this property is set, the object provided is parsed and used. Otherwise this is populated from the API request.

attributes.name: data
attributes.description:
A week of hours transformed to an array with 7 (or 1 if today specified) entries of the following format:
  data[i] = {ymdDate: "YYYY-MM-DD", mdDate: "Mon D", month: "Month name", dayOfWeek: "Monday/Tuesday/...", hours: "8am-10pm", currentStatus: "Open/Closed/Closing Soon/..."}

attributes.name: name
attributes.description: The name of the Library location.

properties.description: The library that is being requested.  If the uuid property is not specified and the library property is, then this is used to define which Library is being requested.

properties.description: The library object as it is represented from the API.  If this property is set, the object provided is parsed and used, otherwise this is populated from the API request.

properties.description: The full name of the Library including any donor title

properties.name: shortName

properties.description: The descriptive information about the library location.

properties.name: donorName

properties.name: email
properties.description: The library email address.

properties.name: rid
properties.description: The library email address string reversed for use with uvalib-liame component.

properties.name: hoursInfo
properties.description: The descriptive hours information for this library; useful for professional schools not using LibCal Hours.

properties.name: libcalId
properties.description: The Springshare library location ID needed to access the location's hours information.

properties.name: imgId
properties.description: The uuid for the main image of the library location.

properties.name: imgAlt
properties.description: The alternative text to be used for the main image of the library location.

properties.name: slug
properties.description: Slug used for building out URL or anchor reference to specific library location.
